The overall construction program was originally estimated at a 15-month term, reserving an additional margin of 3 months for the definitive closing of the sale deeds. All project cost execution is audited monthly through the reports of an independent Quantity Surveyor acting as technical monitor (Project Monitor). The first report issued by said independent professional revalidates the full viability of the developer's budget, ratifying that the works can be completed without material deviations from the declared costs.

Developer Solvency and Guarantee Protection Scheme

The integral development and physical execution of the works is handled by Meeko Construction Limited, a construction and development company wholly owned and managed by the professional Ryan Meehan. The developer has extensive experience of 20 years within the construction industry, having carried out his professional activity both in Ireland and Australia. The company has operated with its own consolidated corporate structure in Irish territory since 2017, with a direct workforce of more than 20 full-time employees. While the firm has an extensive track record in executing single-family residential contracts and large commercial works, the current project represents its first multi-residential development carried out under the dual condition of builder and developer, a strategy aimed at integrating real estate development as the core line of its business.

